CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 23, 1966, pg. 11B reads: "At Employment Workshop At PITT - When a cross-section of Pittsburgh leadership took part in seminars and discussions on the problem of fully integrating Negroes in employment and apprenticeships pattern of the Pittsburgh area during the past three weeks, these were the scenes and principals. The sessions were sponsored by Pittsburgh corporations which have signed Vice President Humphrey's "Plans for Progress" project which stresses equal opportunity in employment..."
TitMainTitle: Man, possibly Leon Haley, standing behind conference table speaking to audience during employment workshop seminar at the University of Pittsburgh
